# Animate.js

A lightweight JavaScript animation library that provides simple and elegant exit animations for DOM elements.

## Features

- ðŸª¶ Lightweight with zero dependencies
- ðŸŽ¯ Simple API
- ðŸŽ¨ Multiple animation effects
- ðŸ“± Works with any HTML element
- âš¡ Performance-focused animations

## Installation

Include the script in your HTML:

```html
<script src="src/animate.js"></script>
```

## Usage

The library exposes an `animate` object globally with various animation methods.

```javascript
// Select an element
const element = document.querySelector('.my-element');

// Apply an animation
animate.fadeOut(element);
```

## Available Animations

### fadeOut(element)
Smoothly fades out an element by reducing its opacity to 0.

```javascript
animate.fadeOut(document.querySelector('.my-element'));
```

### zoomOut(element)
Scales down an element until it disappears.

```javascript
animate.zoomOut(document.querySelector('.my-element'));
```

### slideOut(element)
Slides an element to the right while fading it out.

```javascript
animate.slideOut(document.querySelector('.my-element'));
```

### rotateOut(element)
Rotates an element 360 degrees while scaling it down to zero.

```javascript
animate.rotateOut(document.querySelector('.my-element'));
```

### shrinkAndFadeOut(element)
Simultaneously shrinks and fades out an element.

```javascript
animate.shrinkAndFadeOut(document.querySelector('.my-element'));
```

### flipOut(element)
Flips an element 90 degrees around its Y axis while fading out.

```javascript
animate.flipOut(document.querySelector('.my-element'));
```

### bounceOut(element)
Creates a bounce effect before scaling down to zero.

```javascript
animate.bounceOut(document.querySelector('.my-element'));
```

### slideAndRotateOut(element)
Combines a slide and rotation animation while fading out.

```javascript
animate.slideAndRotateOut(document.querySelector('.my-element'));
```

## Animation Duration

All animations have a default duration of 300ms, except for `bounceOut` which takes 600ms due to its multi-step animation.

## Browser Support

This library uses modern CSS transforms and transitions. It supports all modern browsers:

- Chrome (latest)
- Firefox (latest)
- Safari (latest)
- Edge (latest)

